Potentially required to recreate fits:
    host_result
        Contains the following values: 
            SN_host: Signal to noise ratio of the recovered host spectrum (host_data = data - qso_model)
            rchi2_decomp: Reduced x^2 of the PCA decomposition ((data − host − qso)² / err², divided by (npix − npca_qso − npca_gal))
            frac_host_4200: Fraction of total flux attributable to the host galaxy in a narrow window around 4200 Å (sum(host)/sum(data) over 4160–4210 Å).
            frac_host_5100: Same, but in the 5080–5130 Å window (the classic AGN continuum-luminosity region).
            Dn4000: The 4000 Å break strength, measured from the recovered host template only (mean flux in 4000–4100 Å in f_ν over mean flux in 3850–3950 Å). Values near 1 indicate young/star-forming populations; values approaching ~1.5–2 indicate older, redder stellar populations (more typical of massive ellipticals/bulges).
            sigma: Stellar velocity dispersion of the host galaxy. This is a sizable dispersion — consistent with a massive bulge/elliptical-type host, and via the M–σ relation would imply a substantial black hole mass.
            sigma_err: uncertainty on sigma (from ppxf's formal error × √χ², or from MC resampling if MC=True).
            v_off: Best-fit velocity offset of the host stellar component relative to the systemic redshift z you supplied. A modest offset like this is common (small residual redshift error, or genuine kinematic offset between host and AGN narrow-line redshift).
            v_off_err: Uncertainty on v_off.rchi2_ppxf0.114Reduced χ² of the ppxf fit itself.
            gal_par_[i]:  coefficients on the 5 galaxy PCA eigenspectra (Yip et al. 2004)
            qso_par_[i]: 10 coefficients on the QSO PCA eigenspectra 

    conti_params: Python list of the "best-fit" parameters, obeys following order based on PyQSOFit source code 
        0: Fe_uv_norm
        1: Fe_uv_FWHM
        2: Fe_uv_shift
        3: Fe_op_norm
        4: Fe_op_FWHM
        5: Fe_op_shift
        6: PL_norm (@ 3000 A)
        7: PL_slope (a in (lambda/3000)^slope)
        8: Balmer_norm
        9: Balmer_Te (continuum electron temperature)
        10: Balmer_Tau (continuum optical depth at Balmer edge)
        11: conti_a_0: polynomial coefficient
        12: conti_a_1
        13: conti_a_2
    conti_result: Metadata (ra, dec, ids), SN_ratio_conti, followed by all conti_params and all host_result
        (If you include conti_result, you should be able to not use conti_param or host_result?)

    line_result: Contains the calculated values from fitting emission line complexes, includes a scale, centerwave, and sigma component for each line (lines are determined by line_priors)
        - For line complexes (Ha, Hb, etc., the line_result contains components for both separate lines, (Hb, OIII4959, etc.) and a blended version with all components considered)

    wave: The grid everything else was evaluated on
    flux, err: if you want residuals/χ² or to recompute line_flux

